{"title_page": "Tim Godfrey (musician)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Tim Godfrey\n| background          = solo_singer <!-- mandatory format: please do not change or remove -->\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| birth_name          = Timothy Chukwudi Godfrey\n| alias               = Fearless\n| birth_date          = \n| origin              = \n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Christian hip hop]]|[[urban contemporary gospel]]|[[Contemporary Christian Music|CCM]]|[[contemporary worship music]]|[[Gospel music|gospel]]}}\n| occupation          = {{hlist|Singer-songwriter|[[worship leader]]|musician|producer|[[sound engineer]]}}\n| instrument          = \n| years_active        = 2003\u2013present\n| label               = Rox Nation\n| website             =timgodfreyworldwide.com\n}}\n\n'''Tim Godfrey''' is an Nigerian  gospel singer, music director, songwriter, producer, music teacher, vocal instructor, art training consultant and writer.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Alonge |first1=Ayo |title=My grass to grace story \u2013 Tim Godfrey, gospel musician |url=https://www.sunnewsonline.com/my-grass-to-grace-story-tim-godfrey-gospel-musician/ |website=Sunnews Online |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref> He has been regarded to be the Nigerian version of [[Kirk Franklin]] and [[Tye Tribbett]] musical ideas.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ibori |first1=Diana |title=Tim Godfrey biography |url=https://www.legit.ng/1142503-tim-godfrey-biography.html |website=Legit |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref>. He is best known for his song ''Nara'' in collaboration with [[Travis Greene (musician)|Travis Greene]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Admin |title=American Gospel Singer Travis Greene & Tim Godfrey Performs Nigerian Song \u2018Nara\u2019 Live on Stage |url=https://peoplespostng.com/news/american-gospel-singer-travis-greene-tim-godfrey-performs-nigerian-song-nara-live-on-stage/ |website=Peoples Post Ng |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is the founder and owner of the record label Rox Nation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Admin |title=Tim Godfrey unveils record label |url=http://thenationonlineng.net/tim-godfrey-unveils-record-label-2/ |website=The Nation Online |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref> His recent live show was fearless 2019.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Nigerian gospel musicians]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Godfrey, Tim}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n{{Nigeria-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Tim Godfrey\n| background          = solo_singer <!-- mandatory format: please do not change or remove -->\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| caption             = \n| birth_name          = Timothy Chukwudi Godfrey\n| alias               = Fearless\n| birth_date          = \n| origin              = \n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Christian hip hop]]|[[urban contemporary gospel]]|[[Contemporary Christian Music|CCM]]|[[contemporary worship music]]|[[Gospel music|gospel]]}}\n| occupation          = {{hlist|Singer-songwriter|[[worship leader]]|musician|producer|[[sound engineer]]}}\n| instrument          = \n| years_active        = 2003\u2013present\n| label               = Rox Nation\n| website             =timgodfreyworldwide.com\n}}\n\n'''Tim Godfrey''' is an Nigerian  gospel singer, music director, songwriter, producer, music teacher, vocal instructor, art training consultant and writer.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Alonge |first1=Ayo |title=My grass to grace story \u2013 Tim Godfrey, gospel musician |url=https://www.sunnewsonline.com/my-grass-to-grace-story-tim-godfrey-gospel-musician/ |website=Sunnews Online |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref> He has been regarded to be the Nigerian version of [[Kirk Franklin]] and [[Tye Tribbett]] musical ideas.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ibori |first1=Diana |title=Tim Godfrey biography |url=https://www.legit.ng/1142503-tim-godfrey-biography.html |website=Legit |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref>. He is best known for his song ''Nara'' in collaboration with [[Travis Greene (musician)|Travis Greene]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Admin |title=American Gospel Singer Travis Greene & Tim Godfrey Performs Nigerian Song \u2018Nara\u2019 Live on Stage |url=https://peoplespostng.com/news/american-gospel-singer-travis-greene-tim-godfrey-performs-nigerian-song-nara-live-on-stage/ |website=Peoples Post Ng |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe is the founder and owner of the record label Rox Nation.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Admin |title=Tim Godfrey unveils record label |url=http://thenationonlineng.net/tim-godfrey-unveils-record-label-2/ |website=The Nation Online |accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Nigerian gospel musicians]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Godfrey, Tim}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n{{Nigeria-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Peter deerock", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(I added a recent event hosted by tim godfrey)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Godfrey_(musician)"}
